      "content": "That makes sense. I don't want them to sound like modern people just pretending to be old; it needs to feel visceral. Could you actually write out a short snippet of the dialogue? Maybe three or four characters sitting around a table, maybe at a local diner or someone's office, discussing the specific \"unrest\" they're seeing. I really want to see how they'd actually address the people causing the unrest and what their specific concerns or prejudices would sound like in conversation. Just give me a raw draft of how they'd talk to each other about it.",
